>
>Andrew Haisley (andrewh@gtl.demon.co.uk) wrote:
>
> Does anyone know of a secure encryption technique that allows
> ciphertext to be decrypted using one of two keys. It goes
> without saying that neither key should be easily derivable from
> the other.
>
> Andrew
 
 
   Why not use a 2/3 threshhold scheme to hide the message, and then
prepend the message with one of the 3 shares in the threshhold scheme?
(In practice, for reasonably-long messages, you'd hide the key with the
threshhold scheme, then encrypt with the key.)
 
   --John Kelsey, c445585@mizzou1.missouri.edu
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
